===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] /'kɒm.juˌnɪzm̩/

===Etymology===
A calque of the {{G.}} word ''[[Kommunismus]]'' (from Marx and Engels's ''[http://www.marxists.org/archive/marx/works/1848/communist-manifesto/index.htm Manifesto of the German Communist Party]''), in turn a calque of the {{F.}} word ''[[communisme]]'', which was formed from ''[[commun]]'' ("common"), from {{L.}} ''[[communis]]'', and the suffix [[-isme]] ("[[-ism]]").

[[Image:Hammer_and_sickle.svg|thumb|right|The [[red]] flag, particularly when marked with a [[yellow]] [[hammer]] intersecting a yellow [[sickle]], is an [[icon]]ic [[symbol]] of communism.]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any political philosophy or ideology advocating holding the production of resources collectively. 
# Any political social system that implements a communist political philosophy.
# The international socialist society where classes and the state no longer exist.

